'CAUSE KYLE'S SO BAD.

09:07.267 --> 09:09.235
THAT'S WHY I GIVE THEM
THE FREE SAMPLES ‐‐

09:09.269 --> 09:10.637
SO THEY'LL PLAY HIM.

09:10.670 --> 09:14.107
HE'S A BORN SCIENTIST
LIKE HIS DAD.

09:14.140 --> 09:17.510
YEAH, WELL,
WE ALL HAVE OUR TALENTS.

09:17.544 --> 09:20.380
I USED TO BE IN THE DRUG
BUSINESS, TOO ‐‐ SALES.

09:20.413 --> 09:22.215
OH. WITH WHOM?
UH‐HUH.

09:22.248 --> 09:26.219
A‐A SMALL COMPANY.
IT'S NOT AROUND ANYMORE.

09:26.252 --> 09:29.089
BUT I'M ‐‐ I'M LOOKING
TO GET BACK INTO THE FIELD.

09:29.122 --> 09:31.091
YEAH?
DID YOU DO WELL THERE?

09:31.124 --> 09:32.559
NUMBER ONE,
YEAR AFTER YEAR.

09:32.592 --> 09:33.693
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:33.726 --> 09:36.663
HUH.

09:36.696 --> 09:39.365
LOOK AT THOSE GUYS.

09:39.399 --> 09:40.633
LOOK AT THAT.
THEY COULD BE FRIENDS.

09:40.667 --> 09:44.370
MAYBE. UH,
I ALSO DID MARKETING.

09:44.404 --> 09:46.906
LED THIS HUGE
RE‐BRANDING EFFORT.

09:46.940 --> 09:50.110
WHY ‐‐ WHY ‐‐ WHY DON'T THEY DO
A PLAY‐DATE THING?

09:50.143 --> 09:52.112
LIKE A SLEEPOVER
OR SOMETHING?

09:52.145 --> 09:54.347
THEY SHOULD DO
A SLEEPOVER.

09:54.380 --> 09:57.484
THEY'RE NOT, UH, KITTENS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:57.517 --> 10:01.221
YOU CAN'T JUST PUT THEM IN A BOX
AND SAY "PLAY." [ CHUCKLES ]

10:01.254 --> 10:04.924
WHY NOT? PLEASE?
KYLE NEEDS A FRIEND.

10:04.958 --> 10:06.292
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:06.326 --> 10:08.461
